column20: The various Apps in the toolbox can assist embassies in their efforts to create a business-enabling environment\, remove trade barriers and in matching local and Dutch business partners\, in order to shape the local implementation of the Dutch agenda for Aid\, Trade and Investment. column17: Development of a roadmap for an inclusive and sustainable water governance structure for the river Niger in Niger
column20: The purpose of this project is to contribute an expert planning perspective to the development of a roadmap that will lead to an inclusive and sustainable water governance structure for the river Niger in Niger (country). Good governance of the area of the river is essential for the livelihood of millions of people\, the economy of the country and to prevent conflicts. Especially in the context of rapid climate change and extreme weather (and floods) occurring more often. This project will facilitate the planning process for the development of this roadmap in the beginning of 2021.

column20: The Facility for Infrastructure Development (ORIO) encourages public infrastructure development in upcoming markets and developing countries. ORIO contributes to the development\, construction\, expansion\, operation and maintenance of public infrastructure in these countries. In this way\, ORIO aims to contribute to human development and private sector development. It is untied aid. Netherlands Enterprise Agency administers ORIO at the request of the Ministry of Foreign Affairs of The Netherlands.

column17: Project for the installation of a water retention for the regulation of the Sirba river
column20: The project involves the construction of an earth-filled dam\, due to store approx. 7.5 million m3 of water and the development of 70 hectares of arable land near the village of Toure\, in the municipality of Gotheye (Tillabery\, southwestern Niger).,Il progetto prevede la costruzione di una ritenuta d'acqua in terra per potere stoccare ca. 7\,5 milioni di m3 d'acqua e la sistemazione di 70 ettari di terreni nei pressi del villaggio di Toure\, nel comune di Gotheye\, nella regione sud-occidentale nigerina di Tillabery.
